{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01LTe97fnyGMS3vGSwSsPEZe","type":"tool_result","content":"total 48\ndrwxrwxr-x 12 agent agent 4096 Mar  9 19:53 .\ndrwxr-xr-x  1 agent agent 4096 Mar  9 20:36 ..\ndrwxrwxr-x  9 agent agent 4096 Mar  3 20:51 adapters\ndrwxrwxr-x  2 agent agent 4096 Mar  9 17:20 agent\ndrwxrwxr-x  2 agent agent 4096 Mar  9 20:12 config\ndrwxrwxr-x  2 agent agent 4096 Mar  9 17:44 domain\ndrwxrwxr-x  2 agent agent 4096 Mar  9 17:44 dsl\ndrwxrwxr-x  2 agent agent 4096 Mar  4 17:28 engine\ndrwxrwxr-x  2 agent agent 4096 Mar  2 20:15 evolution\ndrwxrwxr-x  2 agent agent 4096 Mar  9 20:31 logstream\ndrwxrwxr-x  2 agent agent 4096 Mar  9 19:51 ports\ndrwxrwxr-x  2 agent agent 4096 Feb 27 16:12 protocol","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01YDrwufo4EVasQfVLwbPGNy","session_id":"4fdefc21-58a5-4b42-a6f6-efcac5882b09","uuid":"5614fe2d-ba4a-4212-ab4d-243f7dd1a07b"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KQC71K5DnURRhwNzKRSgXa","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# CLAUDE.md\n     2→\n     3→This file provides guidance to Claude Code (claude.ai/code) when working with code in this repository.\n     4→\n     5→## Project Overview\n     6→\n     7→Cloche is a system for grow-coding high quality applications. It provides containerized\n     8→environments for coding agents, a workflow DSL for linking agentic and script-driven\n     9→tasks, validated code pipelines, and self-evolving tooling.\n    10→\n    11→**Language:** Go\n    12→\n    13→**Full design:** `docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md`\n    14→\n    15→## Architecture\n    16→\n    17→Three binaries from one Go module:\n    18→\n    19→- **`cloche`** (CLI) — Short-lived client. Talks to daemon over gRPC. Subcommands: `run`, `status`, `logs`, `stop`.\n    20→- **`cloched`** (Daemon) — Long-running. Manages container lifecycle, collects status, persists state. Does NOT interpret workflow logic.\n    21→- **`cloche-agent`** (In-Container) — Autonomous. Parses workflow DSL, walks the graph, executes steps, streams status back to daemon. Runs to completion without human intervention.\n    22→\n    23→Hexagonal architecture: domain logic is independent of infrastructure. Ports define\n    24→interfaces (ContainerRuntime, RunStore, CaptureStore, AgentAdapter). Adapters implement\n    25→them (Docker, SQLite, gRPC, Claude Code).\n    26→\n    27→```\n    28→cmd/\n    29→  cloche/           # CLI client\n    30→  cloched/          # Daemon\n    31→  cloche-agent/     # In-container entrypoint\n    32→internal/\n    33→  domain/           # Core types (Workflow, Step, Result, Run)\n    34→  ports/            # Interfaces (store, container, agent, notifier)\n    35→  adapters/         # Implementations (docker, sqlite, grpc, agents)\n    36→```\n    37→\n    38→## Workflow DSL\n    39→\n    40→Steps report named results; wiring maps results to next steps. `done` and `abort` are\n    41→built-in terminals. See `docs/workflows.md` for syntax and semantics.\n    42→\n    43→## Project Layout\n    44→\n    45→Cloche-specific files live in `.cloche/` at the project root:\n    46→\n    47→```\n    48→my-project/\n    49→├── .cloche/\n    50→│   ├── develop.cloche      # Workflow definition\n    51→│   ├── Dockerfile           # Container image\n    52→│   ├── prompts/             # Prompt templates for agent steps\n    53→│   ├── overrides/           # Files copied on top of /workspace/ in container\n    54→│   └── <run-id>/            # Runtime state (gitignored)\n    55→├── src/                     # Existing project source (untouched)\n    56→└── CLAUDE.md\n    57→```\n    58→\n    59→## Container Model\n    60→\n    61→One container per workflow run (not per step). The entire project root is copied into the\n    62→container at `/workspace/`, then override files from `.cloche/overrides/` are applied on\n    63→top. Results are extracted to git branches. Network is allowlisted.\n    64→\n    65→## Agent Support\n    66→\n    67→Agent-agnostic. The `AgentAdapter` interface wraps any coding agent. Initial adapters:\n    68→Generic (arbitrary commands) and Claude Code.\n    69→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JP4KapEteMPEP4aikpsVjB","session_id":"4fdefc21-58a5-4b42-a6f6-efcac5882b09","uuid":"0a26818d-4ff6-4b70-aba3-fed37169be3f"}
