{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PcT2SjPvXyRHmrfjpye1x3","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Design: `cloche init`\n     2→\n     3→## Purpose\n     4→\n     5→Scaffold a Cloche project in the current directory so a user can go from\n     6→zero to `cloche run` with minimal setup.\n     7→\n     8→## CLI Interface\n     9→\n    10→```\n    11→cloche init [--workflow <name>] [--image <base-image>]\n    12→```\n    13→\n    14→| Flag | Default | Description |\n    15→|------|---------|-------------|\n    16→| `--workflow` | `develop` | Workflow name; creates `<name>.cloche` |\n    17→| `--image` | `ubuntu:24.04` | Base Docker image for Dockerfile |\n    18→\n    19→No flags required. Bare `cloche init` works with sensible defaults.\n    20→\n    21→## Generated Files\n    22→\n    23→```\n    24→.\n    25→├── <workflow>.cloche\n    26→├── Dockerfile\n    27→└── prompts/\n    28→    ├── implement.md\n    29→    └── fix.md\n    30→```\n    31→\n    32→### Workflow (`develop.cloche`)\n    33→\n    34→Generic 3-step: implement, test, fix loop. Placeholder `make test` command.\n    35→\n    36→```\n    37→workflow \"<name>\" {\n    38→  step implement {\n    39→    prompt = file(\"prompts/implement.md\")\n    40→    results = [success, fail]\n    41→  }\n    42→\n    43→  step test {\n    44→    run = \"make test 2>&1\"\n    45→    results = [success, fail]\n    46→  }\n    47→\n    48→  step fix {\n    49→    prompt = file(\"prompts/fix.md\")\n    50→    max_attempts = \"2\"\n    51→    results = [success, fail, give-up]\n    52→  }\n    53→\n    54→  implement:success -> test\n    55→  implement:fail -> abort\n    56→  test:success -> done\n    57→  test:fail -> fix\n    58→  fix:success -> test\n    59→  fix:fail -> abort\n    60→  fix:give-up -> abort\n    61→}\n    62→```\n    63→\n    64→### Dockerfile\n    65→\n    66→Multi-stage build: copies `cloche-agent` from the cloche builder image,\n    67→installs git and claude-code, creates `agent` user.\n    68→\n    69→```dockerfile\n    70→FROM golang:1.25 AS cloche-builder\n    71→WORKDIR /src\n    72→COPY go.mod go.sum ./\n    73→RUN go mod download\n    74→COPY . .\n    75→RUN CGO_ENABLED=0 go build -o /cloche-agent ./cmd/cloche-agent\n    76→\n    77→FROM <base-image>\n    78→RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y git nodejs npm && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*\n    79→RUN npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code\n    80→COPY --from=cloche-builder /cloche-agent /usr/local/bin/cloche-agent\n    81→RUN useradd -m -s /bin/bash agent\n    82→WORKDIR /workspace\n    83→RUN chown agent:agent /workspace\n    84→USER agent\n    85→```\n    86→\n    87→### Prompt Templates\n    88→\n    89→**`prompts/implement.md`** — Generic implementation prompt with user request\n    90→injection point and basic guidelines.\n    91→\n    92→**`prompts/fix.md`** — Generic fix prompt directing the agent to read\n    93→`.cloche/output/` logs and fix failures.\n    94→\n    95→## Behavior\n    96→\n    97→1. Refuse if `<workflow>.cloche` already exists (don't overwrite user work).\n    98→2. Create `prompts/` directory.\n    99→3. Write all template files.\n   100→4. Print next-steps message explaining what to customize."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JP4KapEteMPEP4aikpsVjB","session_id":"4fdefc21-58a5-4b42-a6f6-efcac5882b09","uuid":"6aeff065-c592-48d1-98b6-80a76ce89652"}
