{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01UqVWz9HQBrfLLBRFurZ6Ce","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Cloche Docker Base Image Design\n     2→\n     3→**Date:** 2026-03-06\n     4→**Status:** Design\n     5→\n     6→## Problem\n     7→\n     8→The default Dockerfile generated by `cloche init` builds `cloche-agent` from the cloche\n     9→Go source inside the image. This only works for the cloche project itself (which has the\n    10→source available). For any other project, the template is broken out of the box.\n    11→\n    12→The root `Dockerfile` (used by the cloche project's own `.cloche/`) makes the same\n    13→mistake, and is also unnecessarily large (based on `golang:1.25` for the final stage).\n    14→\n    15→## Solution\n    16→\n    17→A `cloche-base` image: a minimal Debian-slim image with `git` and `cloche-agent`\n    18→pre-installed. Projects start from this image and add their own tooling on top.\n    19→\n    20→Using `cloche-base` is **not required** — projects may use any Dockerfile they like.\n    21→\n    22→---\n    23→\n    24→## `cloche-base` image contents\n    25→\n    26→Built from `docker/cloche-base/Dockerfile` in the cloche repo.\n    27→\n    28→| Component | Why |\n    29→|-----------|-----|\n    30→| `debian:12-slim` | Small, stable, widely compatible |\n    31→| `git` | Required by `cloche-agent` for branch/commit operations |\n    32→| `ca-certificates` | TLS for any outbound requests agents make |\n    33→| `cloche-agent` binary | The in-container workflow executor |\n    34→| `agent` user | Unprivileged user; workdir `/workspace` owned by `agent` |\n    35→\n    36→**Not included:** Node.js, npm, claude-code, language runtimes, build tools. These are\n    37→project-specific and belong in the project's own Dockerfile.\n    38→\n    39→### `docker/cloche-base/Dockerfile`\n    40→\n    41→```dockerfile\n    42→FROM golang:1.25 AS builder\n    43→WORKDIR /src\n    44→COPY go.mod go.sum ./\n    45→RUN go mod download\n    46→COPY . .\n    47→RUN CGO_ENABLED=0 go build -o /cloche-agent ./cmd/cloche-agent\n    48→\n    49→FROM debian:12-slim\n    50→RUN apt-get update \\\n    51→    && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends git ca-certificates \\\n    52→    && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*\n    53→COPY --from=builder /cloche-agent /usr/local/bin/cloche-agent\n    54→RUN useradd -m -s /bin/bash agent\n    55→WORKDIR /workspace\n    56→RUN chown agent:agent /workspace\n    57→USER agent\n    58→```\n    59→\n    60→Self-contained multi-stage build. No pre-built binary required on the host.\n    61→\n    62→---\n    63→\n    64→## Tags\n    65→\n    66→Both tags are applied on every build:\n    67→\n    68→- `cloche-base:latest`\n    69→- `cloche-base:<version>` — derived from `git describe --tags --always`\n    70→\n    71→Local only for now; registry publishing deferred.\n    72→\n    73→---\n    74→\n    75→## Makefile changes\n    76→\n    77→```makefile\n    78→VERSION ?= $(shell git describe --tags --always 2>/dev/null || echo \"dev\")\n    79→\n    80→docker-base:\n    81→\tdocker build -f docker/cloche-base/Dockerfile \\\n    82→\t\t-t cloche-base:latest \\\n    83→\t\t-t cloche-base:$(VERSION) \\\n    84→\t\t.\n    85→\n    86→docker-build: docker-base\n    87→\tdocker build -t cloche-agent:latest -f .cloche/Dockerfile .\n    88→\n    89→install: build docker-build\n    90→\t...  (unchanged beyond this)\n    91→```\n    92→\n    93→`docker-build` now depends on `docker-base` so the cloche project image is always built\n    94→on top of a fresh base.\n    95→\n    96→---\n    97→\n    98→## Root `Dockerfile` update (cloche project's own image)\n    99→\n   100→The root `Dockerfile` (`.cloche/Dockerfile` for the cloche project) is simplified to"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JP4KapEteMPEP4aikpsVjB","session_id":"4fdefc21-58a5-4b42-a6f6-efcac5882b09","uuid":"5d30ab1a-b84d-49e5-9c4c-47f5395513b7"}
