{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JP4KapEteMPEP4aikpsVjB","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have comprehensive documentation. Let me compile a thorough summary of all the documentation I've read.\n\n## Complete Documentation Summary\n\nI've successfully read all major documentation files from the Cloche repository. Here's a comprehensive overview of what I found:\n\n### **1. CLAUDE.md** (`/workspace/CLAUDE.md`)\nThe project guidance file for Claude Code. Key points:\n- **Cloche** is a system for grow-coding high-quality applications\n- Language: Go\n- Three binaries: `cloche` (CLI), `cloched` (daemon), `cloche-agent` (in-container)\n- Hexagonal architecture with domain logic independent of infrastructure\n- Project layout uses `.cloche/` directory for workflow definitions, Dockerfiles, prompts, and overrides\n- One container per workflow run with file copying and git extraction\n\n### **2. README.md** (`/workspace/README.md`)\nHigh-level project overview:\n- Solves the problem of running coding agents safely and efficiently\n- Provides containerized environments, workflow DSL, validated code pipelines, and self-evolving tooling\n- Three key pillars: isolation, workflows, and validation\n\n### **3. System Design** (`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md`)\nComprehensive MVP architecture covering:\n- **System Components**: Three binaries with specific responsibilities\n  - CLI: Short-lived, talks to daemon over gRPC\n  - Daemon: Long-running, manages containers, persists state, does NOT interpret workflows\n  - Agent: Autonomous, parses DSL, walks graph, executes steps\n- **Communication**: gRPC (CLI<->Daemon) and JSON stdout (Agent<->Daemon)\n- **Workflow DSL**: Graph-based with steps, results, wiring\n- **Hexagonal Architecture**: Domain types isolated from infrastructure\n- **Container Model**: One per run, file isolation, git extraction for results\n- **Capture System**: Records inputs, outputs, results, logs\n- **MVP Scope**: Full feature set for v0.1 with post-MVP roadmap\n\n### **4. Workflows DSL** (`/workspace/docs/workflows.md`)\nComplete workflow specification:\n- **Two location types**:\n  - Container workflows (`.cloche/*.cloche` except `host.cloche`): Run inside Docker\n  - Host workflow (`.cloche/host.cloche`): Runs on host machine\n- **Step Types** (inferred from content):\n  - `agent`: Has `prompt` field\n  - `script`: Has `run` field\n  - `workflow`: Has `workflow_name` field (host only)\n- **DSL Syntax**: Step definitions with results, wiring maps results to next steps\n- **Key Properties**: Type inference, separate wiring, parse-time validation\n- **Execution Model**: Container workflows by agent, host workflows by daemon\n\n### **5. Edge Selection & Fanout Design** (`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-edge-selection-design.md`)\nAdvanced workflow routing:\n- **Result Protocol**: Steps emit `CLOCHE_RESULT:<name>` to select edges\n- **Fallback**: Exit code convention (0=success, non-zero=fail)\n- **Fanout**: Multiple wires from same (step, result) enable parallel execution\n- **Collect**: Synchronization keywords:\n  - `collect all(...)`: Start when every condition met\n  - `collect any(...)`: Start when any condition met\n- **Engine Changes**: From linear loop to concurrent DAG walker\n- **Validation**: All results must be wired, no orphans, reachability checks\n\n### **6. Cloche Init Design** (`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-23-cloche-init-design.md`)\nProject scaffolding tool:\n- Creates `.cloche/` with workflow, Dockerfile, and prompt templates\n- Generic 3-step: implement → test → fix loop\n- Multi-stage Dockerfile: builds from cloche builder image\n- Includes `cloche-agent`, `git`, and `claude-code`\n\n### **7. Self-Evolution System Design** (`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-design.md`)\nPost-run optimization pipeline:\n- **Architecture**: Multi-stage pipeline with LLM-driven evolution\n- **Pipeline**: Collector → Classifier → Reflector → 3-way branching (Prompt/Script/DSL)\n- **ACE Framework**: Uses structured lesson extraction\n- **Scope**: Additive changes only (no removal/mutation)\n- **Multi-project**: Scoped by project_dir + workflow_name\n- **Data Collection**: Captures assembled prompts, LLM responses, retry counts\n\n### **8. Subdirectory Layout & Daemon Extraction** (`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-01-subdirectory-layout-and-poll-design.md`)\nThree related improvements:\n- **Directory Layout**: Move cloche files to `./cloche/` subdirectory\n- **Result Extraction**: Replace in-container git push with daemon-side `docker cp` + host git\n- **Worktrees**: Daemon manages git worktrees in `.gitworktrees/` for concurrency\n- **Poll Command**: New `cloche poll` command blocks until run completes\n\n### **9. Next Features Design** (`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-03-next-features-design.md`)\nFive planned features:\n1. **Orchestrator**: Auto-dispatch tasks, manage merge queue\n   - TaskTracker port with Beads adapter\n   - PromptGenerator for LLM-based prompt creation\n   - Per-project concurrency limits\n2. **Indicator Lights**: Status visualization (not detailed in excerpt)\n3. **Web Dashboard**: Project management UI\n4. **Log Contents**: Comprehensive output capture\n5. **Container Deletion**: Manual cleanup option\n\n### **10. Installation Guide** (`/workspace/docs/INSTALL.md`)\nSetup instructions:\n- **Prerequisites**: Docker, Git, `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`\n- **Installation methods**: Build from source, `go install`, pre-built binaries (planned), Homebrew (planned)\n- **Build requirements**: Go 1.25+\n- **Docker image building**: `make docker-build` for agent image\n\n### **11. Usage Guide** (`/workspace/docs/USAGE.md`)\nComprehensive user documentation:\n- **Quick Start**: Build, start daemon, run workflow, monitor, extract results\n- **Container Isolation**: No bind mounts, copy-in at start, git extraction on completion\n- **CLI Commands**:\n  - `cloche init`: Scaffold project\n  - `cloche run`: Launch workflow\n  - `cloche status`: Check run status\n  - `cloche list`: List runs\n  - `cloche logs`: Show logs with streaming support\n  - `cloche poll`: Wait for completion\n  - `cloche stop`: Cancel run\n  - `cloche delete`: Remove containers\n  - `cloche orchestrate`: Dispatch ready work\n  - `cloche health`: Project health summary\n  - `cloche shutdown`: Stop daemon\n- **Workflow Setup**: Step types, wiring, retry loops, parallel branches, collect\n- **Result Protocol**: `CLOCHE_RESULT:<name>` marker with exit code fallback\n- **Prompt Assembly**: Multi-source prompt construction\n- **Project Layout**: Full directory structure explanation\n- **Configuration**: Environment variables for daemon and client\n\n### **12. Project Pages Design** (`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md`)\nWeb UI for project management:\n- **Route**: `/projects/{name}`\n- **Panels**: Orchestrator control, project info, workflow DAG visualization\n- **API Additions**: Endpoints for orchestrator status, enable/disable, concurrency override\n\n### **13. Cloche Docker Base Design** (`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-cloche-base-docker-design.md`)\nBase image for projects:\n- `cloche-base` image with git and cloche-agent pre-installed\n- Built from `debian:12-slim` with minimal dependencies\n- Projects extend this image with their own tooling\n- Two tags: `latest` and version-based\n\n### **14. Host Workflow Design** (`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md`)\nExtension point for custom orchestration:\n- Special `.cloche/host.cloche` file for host-level workflows\n- New `workflow` step type for dispatching container runs\n- Environment variable injection: `CLOCHE_TASK_ID`, `CLOCHE_TASK_TITLE`, etc.\n- Output capture per step for data passing\n\n### **15. AGENTS.md** (`/workspace/AGENTS.md`)\nAgent development instructions:\n- Uses **beads (bd)** for issue tracking\n- \"Landing the plane\" workflow for session completion\n- MANDATORY: push to remote before ending session\n- Status commands and lifecycle management\n\n### **16. PROJECT.md** (`/workspace/PROJECT.md`)\nHigh-level project roadmap with five next features detailed in the design documents above.\n\n---\n\n## Key Architectural Insights\n\n**Core Philosophy**: Cloche enables autonomous coding while maintaining safety and quality through:\n1. **Containerization**: Complete filesystem isolation, network allowlisting\n2. **Validated Pipelines**: Automatic validation steps and retry loops\n3. **Self-Evolution**: Automatic prompt/workflow improvement based on failures\n4. **Extensibility**: Host workflows allow custom orchestration strategies\n\n**Three Binary Model**:\n- CLI is stateless and short-lived\n- Daemon is the orchestrator and state keeper\n- Agent is autonomous and self-directing\n\n**Workflow Graph Engine**: Supports linear flows, retry loops, parallel branches, and synchronization points with first-class result selection and routing.\n\nAll documentation files are located in `/workspace/docs/` and `/workspace/docs/plans/` directories with the specified absolute paths."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ad031ae1c6c39cae5 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 50278\ntool_uses: 25\nduration_ms: 39888</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4fdefc21-58a5-4b42-a6f6-efcac5882b09","uuid":"6ef98c85-dd4d-4951-b92b-dc9238f18fd4","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read all documentation files in this repo. Specifically:\n1. docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md\n2. docs/workflows.md\n3. CLAUDE.md\n4. Any other .md files in docs/\n5. Any README files\n\nReturn the full content or key sections of each doc file found.","agentId":"ad031ae1c6c39cae5","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have comprehensive documentation. Let me compile a thorough summary of all the documentation I've read.\n\n## Complete Documentation Summary\n\nI've succe