{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01YDrwufo4EVasQfVLwbPGNy","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me compile all this information into a final report.\n\n## Codebase Structure Report\n\nBased on my thorough exploration, here's the complete architecture of the Cloche system:\n\n### **1. Binaries (cmd/)**\n\nLocated in `/workspace/cmd/` - Three binaries from one Go module:\n\n- **`cloche`** (`/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go`): CLI client\n  - Subcommands: `init`, `health`, `run`, `status`, `logs`, `poll`, `list`, `stop`, `delete`, `orchestrate`, `shutdown`\n  - Talks to daemon over gRPC\n  - Files:\n    - `main.go` - CLI entry point with all command implementations\n    - `init.go` - Project initialization\n    - `health.go` - Project health check\n    - `poll.go` - Poll for run completion\n    - Test files for init, health, orchestrate\n\n- **`cloched`** (`/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go`): Daemon\n  - Long-running service managing container lifecycle, status, and state persistence\n  - Initializes runtime (Docker or local), store (SQLite), and gRPC server\n  - Sets up HTTP web dashboard and auto-runs workflows\n  - Implements evolution triggers for self-evolving tooling\n\n- **`cloche-agent`** (`/workspace/cmd/cloche-agent/main.go`): In-container entrypoint\n  - Autonomous agent that parses workflow DSL, walks execution graph, executes steps\n  - Streams status back to daemon\n\n---\n\n### **2. Domain Model (internal/domain/)**\n\nCore types representing the workflow system:\n\n- **`workflow.go`**: Workflow definition and validation\n  - `Workflow` struct with Steps, Wiring, Collects, EntryStep\n  - `Step` struct with Type (agent/script/workflow), Results, Config\n  - `Wire` and `Collect` for control flow\n  - `StepType` enum: StepTypeAgent, StepTypeScript, StepTypeWorkflow\n  - `WorkflowLocation` enum: LocationContainer, LocationHost\n  - Validation methods: `Validate()`, `ValidateLocation()`, `ValidateConfig()`, `NextSteps()`\n\n- **`run.go`**: Execution state and history\n  - `Run` struct with State (pending/running/succeeded/failed/cancelled)\n  - `StepExecution` with result, timestamps, logs, git ref\n  - `RunState` enum with state transitions\n  - Helper methods: `Start()`, `RecordStepStart()`, `RecordStepComplete()`, `Complete()`, `Fail()`\n\n- **`health.go`**: Project health assessment (validation, structure checks)\n- **`namegen.go`**: Generate random run IDs (e.g., develop-bold-reed)\n\n---\n\n### **3. Ports (Interfaces) (internal/ports/)**\n\nHexagonal architecture - define interfaces independent of implementation:\n\n- **`agent.go`**: `AgentAdapter` interface\n  - `Name()` and `Execute(ctx, step, workDir)` → (result, error)\n  - Executes a single agent step inside container\n\n- **`container.go`**: `ContainerRuntime` interface\n  - `Start()`, `Stop()`, `AttachOutput()`, `Wait()`, `CopyFrom()`, `Logs()`, `Remove()`, `Inspect()`\n  - `ImageEnsurer` optional interface for image validation/rebuild\n\n- **`store.go`**: Three store interfaces\n  - `RunStore`: CRUD operations for runs and querying by project\n  - `CaptureStore`: Save/retrieve step execution captures\n  - `LogStore`: Manage log files (full, script, llm types) organized by run/step\n  - `EvolutionStore`: Track workflow evolution history\n\n- **`tracker.go`**: `TaskTracker` interface\n  - `ListReady()`, `Claim()`, `Complete()`, `Fail()`\n  - Integrates external task tracking (e.g., Beads issue tracker)\n\n---\n\n### **4. Adapters (internal/adapters/)**\n\nImplementations of the port interfaces:\n\n#### **Container Runtimes:**\n- **`docker/`** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/`)\n  - `runtime.go`: Docker container management via `docker` CLI\n  - `build.go`: Build Docker images from project Dockerfile\n  - `extract.go`: Extract results from completed containers\n\n- **`local/`** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/local/`)\n  - `runtime.go`: Direct process execution (no containers) for local development\n\n#### **Data Stores:**\n- **`sqlite/`** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/`)\n  - `store.go`: SQLite-backed persistent storage\n    - Tables: runs, step_executions, log_files, evolution tables\n    - WAL mode for concurrent access with single connection serialization\n    - Implements `RunStore`, `CaptureStore`, `LogStore`, `EvolutionStore`\n\n#### **Communication:**\n- **`grpc/`** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/`)\n  - `server.go`: gRPC service implementation\n    - Methods: RunWorkflow, GetStatus, ListRuns, StreamLogs, StopRun, DeleteContainer, Orchestrate, Shutdown\n    - Manages run lifecycle and streams output\n\n- **`web/`** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/`)\n  - `handler.go`: HTTP handlers for web dashboard and REST API\n  - Includes SSE streaming for live logs\n  - Template-based UI and JSON responses\n  - Supporting templates and static assets\n\n#### **Agent Adapters:**\n- **`agents/generic/`** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/generic/`)\n  - Generic shell command executor (run: \"script\")\n  - Parses result markers from stdout\n\n- **`agents/prompt/`** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/prompt/`)\n  - Claude Code agent adapter\n  - Assembles prompts from templates and user input\n  - Handles streaming output parsing (stream-json format)\n  - Implements retry logic with max_attempts\n  - Fallback chain support (multiple agent commands)\n\n#### **Task Tracker:**\n- **`beads/`** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/beads/`)\n  - `tracker.go`: JSONL-based issue tracker integration\n  - Stores issues in `.beads/issues.jsonl`\n  - Supports dependencies and status tracking\n\n---\n\n### **5. Execution Engine (internal/)**\n\n- **`engine/`** - `engine.go`:\n  - Core workflow execution engine\n  - `StepExecutor` interface for step execution\n  - `StatusHandler` for progress notifications\n  - Manages concurrent step execution, fan-out, and collects\n  - Default timeout: 30 minutes per step\n\n- **`agent/`** - `runner.go`:\n  - In-container agent that runs workflows\n  - Reads .cloche workflow files, parses DSL, executes steps sequentially/parallel\n  - Records execution history to disk\n\n- **`dsl/`** - Workflow DSL parser and lexer:\n  - `lexer.go`: Tokenize workflow syntax\n  - `parser.go`: Parse DSL into Workflow domain objects\n  - `mutator.go`: Transform workflows (e.g., for fan-out)\n  - `token.go`: Token type definitions\n\n- **`logstream/`** - Log collection and streaming:\n  - `parse.go`: Parse Claude Code's stream-json output format\n  - `broadcaster.go`: SSE event distribution for live log streaming\n  - `logstream.go`: Core log handling\n\n- **`evolution/`** - Self-evolution and workflow improvement:\n  - `trigger.go`: Detects when to trigger workflow evolution\n  - `orchestrator.go`: Coordinates evolution runs\n  - `classifier.go`: Classifies run outcomes\n  - `collector.go`: Collects workflow changes\n  - `reflector.go`: Analyzes run results\n  - `audit.go`, `curator.go`, `scriptgen.go`, `llmclient.go`: Supporting utilities\n\n- **`protocol/`** - Inter-process communication:\n  - `result.go`: CLOCHE_RESULT marker for step results\n  - `status.go`: StatusWriter for streaming status updates\n  - `history.go`: Run history recording\n\n- **`config/`** - Global and project configuration:\n  - `config.go`: Load config from `~/.config/cloche/config` and `.cloche/config.toml`\n\n---\n\n### **6. API (api/)**\n\n- **`proto/`** - Protocol buffer definitions\n- **`clochepb/`** - Generated gRPC code\n  - `cloche.pb.go`: Message definitions\n  - `cloche_grpc.pb.go`: gRPC service stubs and implementations\n\n---\n\n### **7. .cloche/ Directory (Project Structure)**\n\nLocated at `/workspace/.cloche/`:\n\n```\n.cloche/\n├── develop.cloche          # Container workflow: implement → test → fix → update-docs → done\n├── host.cloche            # Host workflow: prepare-prompt → develop → merge → done\n├── Dockerfile             # Container image definition\n├── config.toml            # Project config\n├── prompts/\n│   ├── implement.md       # Claude prompt for implementation\n│   ├── fix.md            # Claude prompt for bug fixing\n│   └── update-docs.md    # Claude prompt for documentation\n├── overrides/             # Files overlaid on /workspace in container\n├── scripts/              # Helper scripts (prepare-prompt.sh, merge-to-main.sh)\n├── output/               # Step output logs\n├── attempt_count/        # Retry attempt tracking\n├── prompts.txt           # User-provided prompt\n├── history.log           # Execution history\n└── <run-id>/            # Runtime directories for each run\n    ├── prompt.txt       # User prompt for this run\n    └── state/          # Step execution captures\n```\n\n---\n\n### **8. Key Files Summary**\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` | CLI client entry point with all commands |\n| `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go` | Daemon initialization and server setup |\n| `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go` | Workflow AST and validation |\n| `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` | Run execution state machine |\n| `/workspace/internal/ports/*.go` | Interface definitions (4 files) |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/runtime.go` | Docker container implementation |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go` | SQLite persistence layer |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` | gRPC service implementation |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` | HTTP API and web dashboard |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt.go` | Claude Code agent integration |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/generic/generic.go` | Shell script executor |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/beads/tracker.go` | Issue tracker integration |\n| `/workspace/internal/engine/engine.go` | Workflow execution engine |\n| `/workspace/internal/agent/runner.go` | In-container agent runner |\n| `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go` | Workflow DSL parser |\n| `/workspace/internal/evolution/trigger.go` | Workflow evolution trigger |\n| `/workspace/api/clochepb/cloche_grpc.pb.go` | Generated gRPC code |\n\n---\n\n### **Architecture Summary**\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    cloche (CLI Client)                       │\n│                    Sends commands via gRPC                   │\n└──────────────────────┬──────────────────────────────────────┘\n                       │ gRPC\n       ┌───────────────┼───────────────┐\n       │               │               │\n┌──────▼──────┐  ┌─────▼──────┐  ┌───▼──────────┐\n│  cloched    │  │   gRPC     │  │  Web Handler │\n│  (Daemon)   │  │  Server    │  │  (HTTP/SSE)  │\n└──────┬──────┘  └────────────┘  └──────────────┘\n       │\n       ├─── ContainerRuntime (Docker or Local)\n       ├─── RunStore (SQLite)\n       ├─── LogStore (SQLite)\n       ├─── EvolutionStore (SQLite)\n       │\n       └─── in-container:\n            ├── Agent Runner\n            ├── Workflow Engine\n            ├── AgentAdapter (prompt, generic, script)\n            └── Results pushed to git branches\n```\n\nThis is a sophisticated grow-coding system combining containerized environments, agentic execution, self-evolution, and validated pipelines in ~4700 lines of Go code across 159 Go files."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: aba14061f56c50153 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 64392\ntool_uses: 36\nduration_ms: 79075</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4fdefc21-58a5-4b42-a6f6-efcac5882b09","uuid":"23b60dbd-6158-411d-9229-f81fd492848a","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the codebase structure thoroughly. I need to understand:\n1. What binaries exist under cmd/\n2. What's in internal/ (domain, ports, adapters)\n3. What CLI subcommands exist for the cloche binary\n4. What interfaces exist in ports/\n5. What adapters exist\n6. What's in .cloche/ directory\n\nFocus o