m: StepTypeAgent, StepTypeScript, StepTypeWorkflow\n  - `WorkflowLocation` enum: LocationContainer, LocationHost\n  - Validation methods: `Validate()`, `ValidateLocation()`, `ValidateConfig()`, `NextSteps()`\n\n- **`run.go`**: Execution state and history\n  - `Run` struct with State (pending/running/succeeded/failed/cancelled)\n  - `StepExecution` with result, timestamps, logs, git ref\n  - `RunState` enum with state transitions\n  - Helper methods: `Start()`, `RecordStepStart()`, `RecordStepComplete()`, `Complete()`, `Fail()`\n\n- **`health.go`**: Project health assessment (validation, structure checks)\n- **`namegen.go`**: Generate random run IDs (e.g., develop-bold-reed)\n\n---\n\n### **3. Ports (Interfaces) (internal/ports/)**\n\nHexagonal architecture - define interfaces independent of implementation:\n\n- **`agent.go`**: `AgentAdapter` interface\n  - `Name()` and `Execute(ctx, step, workDir)` → (result, error)\n  - Executes a single agent step inside container\n\n- **`container.go`**: `ContainerRuntime` interface\n  - `Start()`, `Stop()`, `AttachOutput()`, `Wait()`, `CopyFrom()`, `Logs()`, `Remove()`, `Inspect()`\n  - `ImageEnsurer` optional interface for image validation/rebuild\n\n- **`store.go`**: Three store interfaces\n  - `RunStore`: CRUD operations for runs and querying by project\n  - `CaptureStore`: Save/retrieve step execution captures\n  - `LogStore`: Manage log files (full, script, llm types) organized by run/step\n  - `EvolutionStore`: Track workflow evolution history\n\n- **`tracker.go`**: `TaskTracker` interface\n  - `ListReady()`, `Claim()`, `Complete()`, `Fail()`\n  - Integrates external task tracking (e.g., Beads issue tracker)\n\n---\n\n### **4. Adapters (internal/adapters/)**\n\nImplementations of the port interfaces:\n\n#### **Container Runtimes:**\n- **`docker/`** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/`)\n  - `runtime.go`: Docker container management via `docker` CLI\n  - `build.go`: Build Docker images from project Dockerfile\n  - `extract.go`: Extract results from completed containers\n\n- **`local/`** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/local/`)\n  - `runtime.go`: Direct process execution (no containers) for local development\n\n#### **Data Stores:**\n- **`sqlite/`** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/`)\n  - `store.go`: SQLite-backed persistent storage\n    - Tables: runs, step_executions, log_files, evolution tables\n    - WAL mode for concurrent access with single connection serialization\n    - Implements `RunStore`, `CaptureStore`, `LogStore`, `EvolutionStore`\n\n#### **Communication:**\n- **`grpc/`** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/`)\n  - `server.go`: gRPC service implementation\n    - Methods: RunWorkflow, GetStatus, ListRuns, StreamLogs, StopRun, DeleteContainer, Orchestrate, Shutdown\n    - Manages run lifecycle and streams output\n\n- **`web/`** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/`)\n  - `handler.go`: HTTP handlers for web dashboard and REST API\n  - Includes SSE streaming for live logs\n  - Template-based UI and JSON responses\n  - Supporting templates and static assets\n\n#### **Agent Adapters:**\n- **`agents/generic/`** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/generic/`)\n  - Generic shell command executor (run: \"script\")\n  - Parses result markers from stdout\n\n- **`agents/prompt/`** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/prompt/`)\n  - Claude Code agent adapter\n  - Assembles prompts from templates and user input\n  - Handles streaming output parsing (stream-json format)\n  - Implements retry logic with max_attempts\n  - Fallback chain support (multiple agent commands)\n\n#### **Task Tracker:**\n- **`beads/`** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/beads/`)\n  - `tracker.go`: JSONL-based issue tracker integration\n  - Stores issues in `.beads/issues.jsonl`\n  - Supports dependencies and status tracking\n\n---\n\n### **5. Execution Engine (internal/)**\n\n- **`engine/`** - `engine.go`:\n  - Core workflow execution engine\n  - `StepExecutor` interface for step execution\n  - `StatusHandler