  # Implementations (docker, local, sqlite, grpc, web, agents, beads)\n    36→```\n    37→\n    38→## Workflow DSL\n    39→\n    40→Steps report named results; wiring maps results to next steps. `done` and `abort` are\n    41→built-in terminals. See `docs/workflows.md` for syntax and semantics.\n    42→\n    43→## Project Layout\n    44→\n    45→Cloche-specific files live in `.cloche/` at the project root:\n    46→\n    47→```\n    48→my-project/\n    49→├── .cloche/\n    50→│   ├── develop.cloche      # Container workflow definition\n    51→│   ├── host.cloche          # Host workflow definition\n    52→│   ├── config.toml          # Project configuration\n    53→│   ├── Dockerfile           # Container image\n    54→│   ├── prompts/             # Prompt templates for agent steps\n    55→│   ├── scripts/             # Helper scripts for host workflow steps\n    56→│   ├── overrides/           # Files copied on top of /workspace/ in container\n    57→│   └── <run-id>/            # Runtime state (gitignored)\n    58→├── src/                     # Existing project source (untouched)\n    59→└── CLAUDE.md\n    60→```\n    61→\n    62→## Container Model\n    63→\n    64→One container per workflow run (not per step). The entire project root is copied into the\n    65→container at `/workspace/`, then override files from `.cloche/overrides/` are applied on\n    66→top. Results are extracted to git branches. Network is allowlisted.\n    67→\n    68→## Agent Support\n    69→\n    70→Agent-agnostic. The `AgentAdapter` interface wraps any coding agent. Initial adapters:\n    71→Generic (arbitrary commands) and Claude Code.\n    72→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4fdefc21-58a5-4b42-a6f6-efcac5882b09","uuid":"abd776fa-87b7-4e51-89b3-a94067d5158b","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/CLAUDE.md","content":"# CLAUDE.md\n\nThis file provides guidance to Claude Code (claude.ai/code) when working with code in this repository.\n\n## Project Overview\n\nCloche is a system for grow-coding high quality applications. It provides containerized\nenvironments for coding agents, a workflow DSL for linking agentic and script-driven\ntasks, validated code pipelines, and self-evolving tooling.\n\n**Language:** Go\n\n**Full design:** `docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md`\n\n## Architecture\n\nThree binaries from one Go module:\n\n- **`cloche`** (CLI) — Short-lived client. Talks to daemon over gRPC. Subcommands: `init`, `health`, `run`, `status`, `logs`, `poll`, `list`, `stop`, `delete`, `orchestrate`, `shutdown`.\n- **`cloched`** (Daemon) — Long-running. Manages container lifecycle, collects status, persists state. Does NOT interpret workflow logic.\n- **`cloche-agent`** (In-Container) — Autonomous. Parses workflow DSL, walks the graph, executes steps, streams status back to daemon. Runs to completion without human intervention.\n\nHexagonal architecture: domain logic is independent of infrastructure. Ports define\ninterfaces (ContainerRuntime, RunStore, CaptureStore, LogStore, EvolutionStore, AgentAdapter, TaskTracker). Adapters implement\nthem (Docker, Local, SQLite, gRPC, Web, Generic agent, Prompt agent, Beads tracker).\n\n```\ncmd/\n  cloche/           # CLI client\n  cloched/          # Daemon\n  cloche-agent/     # In-container entrypoint\ninternal/\n  domain/           # Core types (Workflow, Step, Result, Run)\n  ports/            # Interfaces (store, container, agent, tracker)\n  adapters/         # Implementations (docker, local, sqlite, grpc, web, agents, beads)\n```\n\n## Workflow DSL\n\nSteps report named results; wiring maps results to next steps. `done` and `abort` are\nbuilt-in terminals. See `docs/workflows.md` for syntax and semantics.\n\n## Project Layout\n\nCloche-specific files live in `.cloche/` at the project root:\n\n```\nmy-project/\n├── .cloche/\n│   ├── develop.cloche      # Container workflow definition\n│   ├── host.cloche          # Host workflow definition\n│   ├── config.toml          # Project configuration\n│   ├── Dockerfile           # Container image\n│   ├── prompts/             # Prompt templates for agent steps\n│   ├── scripts/             # Helper scripts for host workflow steps\n│   ├── overrides/           # Files copied on top of /workspace/ in container\n│   └── <run-id>/            # Runtime state (gitignored)\n├── src/                     # Existing project source (untouched)\n└── CLAUDE.md\n```\n\n## Container Model\n\nOne container per workflow run (not per step). The entire project root is copied into the\ncontainer at `/workspace/`, then override files from `.cloche/overrides/` are applied on\ntop. Results are extracted to git branches. Network is allowlisted.\n\n## Agent Support\n\nAgent-agnostic. The `AgentAdapter` interface wraps any coding agent. Initial adapters:\nGeneric (arbitrary commands) and Claude Code.\n","numLines":72,"startLine":1,"totalLines":72}}}
